import { defineNuxtPlugin } from '#app/nuxt'
import { LazyButton, LazyLogo, LazyAppArticle, LazyAppCTA, LazyAppContent, LazyAppContentImage, LazyAppHero, LazyAppRow, LazyAppSocials, LazyAppText, LazyAppFooterMenu, LazyAppNavigationHamburger, LazyAppNavigationMenu, LazyAppNavigationMenuItem, LazyAppNavigationRoutes, LazyIcon, LazyIconCSS } from '#components'
const lazyGlobalComponents = [
  ["Button", LazyButton],
["Logo", LazyLogo],
["AppArticle", LazyAppArticle],
["AppCTA", LazyAppCTA],
["AppContent", LazyAppContent],
["AppContentImage", LazyAppContentImage],
["AppHero", LazyAppHero],
["AppRow", LazyAppRow],
["AppSocials", LazyAppSocials],
["AppText", LazyAppText],
["AppFooterMenu", LazyAppFooterMenu],
["AppNavigationHamburger", LazyAppNavigationHamburger],
["AppNavigationMenu", LazyAppNavigationMenu],
["AppNavigationMenuItem", LazyAppNavigationMenuItem],
["AppNavigationRoutes", LazyAppNavigationRoutes],
["Icon", LazyIcon],
["IconCSS", LazyIconCSS],
  
]

export default defineNuxtPlugin({
  name: 'nuxt:global-components',
  setup (nuxtApp) {
    for (const [name, component] of lazyGlobalComponents) {
      nuxtApp.vueApp.component(name, component)
      nuxtApp.vueApp.component('Lazy' + name, component)
    }
  }
})
